history.content: I'm an MSE major and I chose to enroll in this semester's EE16A after the adjustment period and I still got in. I think what you need to do is pick a lab section with the most empty seats. Also I heard that there are usually seats in the course reserved for other engineering majors but I'm not entirely sure about the credibility of the source.I don't think it'll be too hard to get in even without phase I, but I might just be lucky.

https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/eecs/degree-reqs/enrollment-policy

Some seats are reserved for COE students. Those seats filled during Phase I for Spring '17. As the student said above, being strategic with secondary section choice is highly recommended. EE16A had some seats left in both Fall '16 and Spring '17, but you would need to be flexible with your schedule.

I am a mechanical engineering student (will be a junior in Fall) that needs to take 16A as part of my major. How difficult will it be for me to enroll in 16A next fall? Is it recommended for me to Phase I this course? Or should I wait until next spring instead?
history.subject: EE16A in Fall 2017 for non EECS majors
